#: ../../create-board.rst:2
msgid "Create a Board"
msgstr ""

#: ../../create-board.rst:4
msgid "Open the board editor from the Project manager."
msgstr ""

#: ../../create-board.rst:9
msgid "Draw a Board Outline"
msgstr ""

#: ../../create-board.rst:11
msgid ""
"Draw a outline by first selecting the \"Outline\" Layer in the Layers "
"Panel and then selecting the \"Draw polygon rectangle\" Tool by typing :"
"kbd:`d Y` (or use the Spacebar menu):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../create-board.rst:16
msgid "Place the Packages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../create-board.rst:18
msgid ""
"Place packages on the board using by typing :kbd:`p p` (this time it "
"stands for \"Place Package\"). If you still have the Schematic Editor "
"open you can also select a Symbol and use the \"Place on Board\" Tool by "
"clicking it's button in the top bar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../create-board.rst:20
msgid ""
"If you select Parts in the Schematic Editor they will also be highlighted "
"in the Board Editor. If you change something in the Schematic Editor "
"bring the changes from the schematic to the board, by saving the "
"schematic and clicking 'reload netlist' in the board editor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../create-board.rst:24
msgid ""
"If you want to place a part on the bottom of the board, press :kbd:`e` to "
"flip it to the bottom side. If you are working a lot on the bottom you "
"can use the \"View bottom\" tool to flip the whole board around."
msgstr ""

#: ../../create-board.rst:27
msgid "Add Planes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../create-board.rst:29
msgid ""
"If you want to use a Ground Plane now would be a good time to add it:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../create-board.rst:31
msgid ""
"Select the layer you want to have the plane on (Top- or Bottom-Copper)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../create-board.rst:32
msgid "Draw a polygon rectangle by typing :kbd:`d Y`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../create-board.rst:33
msgid ""
"Right-Click one of the Edges of the newly added polygon and select \"Add "
"Plane\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../create-board.rst:34
msgid ""
"In the Window that pops up select the GND net (if it is not there you "
"didn't add the power net in the Schematic)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../create-board.rst:38
msgid ""
"If the solid filled color of the plane annoys you, you can switch the "
"display style to something else by clicking onto the colored square left "
"of the layer:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../create-board.rst:43
msgid "Route the Nets"
msgstr ""

#: ../../create-board.rst:45
msgid ""
"To route tracks between the parts you connected in the Schematic, type :"
"kbd:`x` and drag from any pin that starts an airwire:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../create-board.rst:51
msgid ""
"The track will always be routed on the layer you have selected, you can "
"quickly select the Top Copper Layer by pressing :kbd:`1` and the Bottom "
"Copper Layer by pressing :kbd:`2`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../create-board.rst:53
msgid ""
"If you want to change sides in the middle of a track you can place a via "
"by pressing :kbd:`v` and then the number of the layer you want to "
"continue."
msgstr ""

#: ../../create-board.rst:57
msgid ""
"Once you are done, check out the 3D view of your part, and export Gerbers "
"using the menu point \"Fabrication Output\" in the application menu."
msgstr ""

